title: For Sale:  Hornady 45230 45Cal 300 GR HP/XTP box of 50
postcontent:
shipping $5.00
will combine shipping
new in factory box

Hornady XTP bullets were designed for hunting, self-defense, and law enforcement. One of the great things about the XTP bullet is reliable performance, it features controlled expansion where six serrations divide the bullet into six symmetrical sections. These sections weaken the jacket to allow controlled expansion at low velocities and ensures fragmentation does not occur at high velocities. The XTP bullet is really known for its stopping power. They were designed from the beginning to expand reliably at a variety of handgun velocities and deliver deep, terminal penetration with every shot. Most handgun bullets are designed to perform at a single factory-specified velocity where the XTP bullet is designed to offer controlled expansion over a range of velocities. 

Each XTP Bullet has a swaged core and drawn copper jacket to ensure uniform expansion and in-flight stability. Adding a cannelure to this bullet keeps the core and the jacket locked together while also allowing the cartridge case to tightly crimp, adding security at high velocities. This is not loaded ammunition.

postcontent:
New in the factory box, unfired 223/5.56 CMMG 16" barrel flat top AR15 carbine with the 6 position collapsible stock. This is the "LE" Law Enforcement model carbine and comes in the extremely durable black "Nitrided" WASP finish. This flat top rifle does not have sights and is ready for the install of any scope, optical sight, or any peep sight of your choosing. This comes with one new 30-round P-Mag magazine, 5 new 20-round Thermold magazines, and 100 rounds of FMJ ammunition.

W.A.S.P. Treated Barrel
(Weapon Armament Surface Protection) is a salt bath ferritic nitrocarburizing surface conversion process or more commonly referred to as nitriding. The nitriding conversion is applied to the barrel inside and out, along with the front sight base on our LE rifles and uppers. Nitriding offers improved wear, abrasion, and corrosion resistance when compared to hard chrome lining or phosphating.

Unlike chrome lining, where the chrome is built up on the surface, nitriding converts the surface without the risk of dimensional build up. CMMG Pioneered the use of this nitriding process on AR barrels and has been using it for many years.

Partial trades will be considered but I prefer a cash sale.

title: For Sale:  Hard to find 9mm Hornady Custom 147 grain XTP boxes of 25
location: boulder, denver north, sportsmen's thonton, Denver, Colorado
postcontent:
I have 5 boxes for sale of the nearly impossible to find Hornady Custom 9mm ammo.

If you know Hornady you know that this is some of their finest.

Plus side is that this is a nice defense round, great for your concealed carry weapon. Also the brass is some of the highest quality for reloading. Each round is produced for consistency and proven reliability. Lots of knock down power, and very accurate.

postcontent:
PMAG 30 M3. Brand New in Package gen 3 PMAGS!
$60.00 each or 10 or more for $55 a piece. (20 available)

Magpul is pleased to announce the latest addition to the PMAG family: the PMAG 30 M3. Like its predecessors, the PMAG 30 M3 is a lightweight 5.56 x 45 NATO / .223 Remington 30-round polymer magazine for the AR15/M16 platform, but with a number of new features which improve its durability, compatibility, and overall performance for the most demanding professional shooters. By combining the knowledge gained from years of PMAG production, extensive research and development of materials and manufacturing processes, and incorporating feedback from a broad range of end-users, the PMAG 30 M3 pushes the envelope of magazine performance one step further.

The PMAG 30 M3 features a corrosion-resistant stainless steel spring, four-way anti-tilt follower, pop-off Impact/Dust Cover that snaps onto the floorplate when not in use, and easy tool-less disassembly for cleaning and maintenance. Low-profile ribs and aggressive front and rear texture provide positive control of the magazine while helping ensure compatibility with common double and triple magazine pouches. The easy to disassemble standard flared floorplate provides drop protection and aids extraction from magazine pouches, but can be replaced by a PMAG Ranger Plate for improved handling, or the new M3 Slim-line floor plate to minimize bulk (not included). A paint pen dot matrix (click here for marking guide) has been added to the bottom panel of the magazine body for easy marking by the end user for magazine identification.

Due to recent legislation which is highly likely to become law soon in Colorado Magpul may be forced to leave the state or go out of business. What this means for the future of these fantastic magazines is unknown. Magpul being the Great company they are will do there best to get production up and running again as soon as possible (currently 1,000,000 Pmags on back order), but will it be before a possible mag ban comes down from the federal government....I sure hope so. Please write the politicians in Colorado and tell them NOT to do this.....

Update: Magpul announced they will be moving there company to a different state! Until the day the new law actually goes into affect Magpul will be selling all the mags they are producing to colorado residents, so they can get as many in the hands of the citizens there as possible. This is an awesome move for a company to go the extra mile to help the citizens there.

Between the move of the company and the fact that Colorado residents will have first dips on what is being produced, it will probabaly be quite a while before mags begin to ship out to the rest of the country again.
